</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36E27AA6A10FFA052E83ACE0686FC71" pageId="7" pageNumber="349" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCB74216A10FFA052E83ACE0686FC71" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="7" pageNumber="349">
<emphasis id="B900A8336A10FFA052E83ACE0627FD51" bold="true" box="[199,308,691,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="349">Remarks</emphasis>
. The 
<taxonomicName id="4C740FA26A10FFA0535B3ACE0521FD51" box="[372,562,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lamprolonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B900A8336A10FFA0535B3ACE0521FD51" box="[372,562,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="349">Lamprolonchaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fauna of the Oceania region is not well known. Although McAlpine described some twelve species from the area (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE509D06A10FFA0500F3AAA05F6FD6E" author="McAlpine, J. F." box="[544,741,727,754]" pageId="7" pageNumber="349" pagination="661 - 700" refId="ref10624" refString="McAlpine, J. F. (1964 a) Descriptions of New Lonchaeidae (Diptera). I. The Canadian Entomologist, 96 (4), 661 - 700. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 96661 - 4" type="journal article" year="1964">McAlpine, 1964a</bibRefCitation>
) there have been few further records since that time apart from those from 
<collectingCountry id="F36334B16A10FFA0533A3A86062FFC89" box="[277,316,763,789]" name="Fiji" pageId="7" pageNumber="349">Fiji</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE509D06A10FFA053653A86050AFC89" author="MacGowan, I." box="[330,537,763,789]" pageId="7" pageNumber="349" pagination="537 - 552" refId="ref10273" refString="MacGowan, I. (2014) The Lonchaeidae of Fiji (Diptera: Schizophora). Zootaxa, 3814 (4), 537 - 552. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3814.4.6" type="journal article" year="2014">MacGowan, 2014</bibRefCitation>
). The original species descriptions by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE509D06A10FFA051EF3A860397FC89" author="McAlpine, J. F." box="[960,1156,763,789]" pageId="7" pageNumber="349" pagination="661 - 700" refId="ref10624" refString="McAlpine, J. F. (1964 a) Descriptions of New Lonchaeidae (Diptera). I. The Canadian Entomologist, 96 (4), 661 - 700. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 96661 - 4" type="journal article" year="1964">McAlpine, 1964a</bibRefCitation>
were rather brief and did not include any illustrations of the male genitalia, although it is possible to identify some of the species from drawings made in his PhD thesis (McAlpine, 1962). It is perhaps not surprising that further species are still to be found. 
<taxonomicName id="4C740FA26A10FFA057A93B3E07D2FC1D" authorityName="MacGowan" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lamprolonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vila">
<emphasis id="B900A8336A10FFA057A93B3E07D2FC1D" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="349">L. vila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with its completely black legs is perhaps most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C740FA26A10FFA051103B1A0367FC1D" authority="McAlpine, 1964" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="1964" box="[831,1140,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lamprolonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ustulata">
<emphasis id="B900A8336A10FFA051103B1A04A5FC1D" box="[831,950,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="349">L. ustulata</emphasis>
McAlpine, 1964
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C740FA26A10FFA056863B1A07DCFC39" authority="McAlpine, 1964" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="1964" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lamprolonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lustrata">
<emphasis id="B900A8336A10FFA056863B1A020EFC1D" box="[1193,1309,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="349">L. lustrata</emphasis>
McAlpine, 1964
</taxonomicName>
but as with all 
<taxonomicName id="4C740FA26A10FFA053563BF60524FC39" box="[377,567,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lamprolonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B900A8336A10FFA053563BF60524FC39" box="[377,567,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="349">Lamprolonchaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species dissection of the male terminalia is required to confirm identification. 
<taxonomicName id="4C740FA26A10FFA052B83BD207CCFC55" authorityName="MacGowan" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,223,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Lamprolonchaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vila">
<emphasis id="B900A8336A10FFA052B83BD207CCFC55" box="[151,223,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="349">L. vila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with its distinctive phallus and rather circular exterior lobe of the surstyli is easily distinguished from other members of the genus.
</paragraph>
